airs (2017\u2013present), and the former Shadow Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness (2015\u20132016) and [[Minister of Veterans Affairs (Canada)|Minister of Veterans Affairs]] (2015). He placed third in the [[2017 Conservative Party of Canada leadership election|2017 Conservative leadership election]]. Prior to entering politics, O'Toole served as a [[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|captain]] in the [[Royal Canadian Air Force]] and was a lawyer after completing military service.<ref name=\"starpros\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/politics/federal/2019/12/12/rona-ambrose-peter-mackay-erin-otoole-cited-as-possible-contenders-to-replace-andrew-scheer-as-conservative-leader.html|title=Rona Ambrose, Peter MacKay, Erin O'Toole cited as possible contenders to replace Andrew Scheer as Conservative Leader|date=12 December 2019|work=Toronto Star|access-date=12 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n:'''Candidacy announced:''' 25 January 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/davidakin/status/1221100162271121410|title=And @ErinOTooleMP makes it official|last=Akin  |first=David|date=25 January 2020|website=@davidakin|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6461702/erin-otoole-conservative-leadership-bid/|title=Erin O'Toole to announce formal bid for Conservative leadership|last=Jackson|first=Hannah|date=25 January 2020|website=Global News|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n:'''Date registered with Elections Canada:'''\n:'''Campaign website:''' [https://erinotoole.ca/ www.erinotoole.ca]\n;Policies:\n:;Economic\n:*Defund the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]]<ref>{{cite web |title=ADD YOUR NAME: I SUPPORT DEFUNDING CBC |url=https://erinotoole.ca/defundcbc/ |website=Erin O'Toole}}</ref><br>\n:*Repeal the carbon tax<ref>{{cite web |title=NO CARBON TAX |url=https://erinotoole.ca/carbontax/ |website=Erin O'Toole}}</ref><br>\n:*End subsidies for media companies<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Toole |first1=Erin |title=Justin Trudeau helps failing media corporations.I'll help working Canadians.https://www.thepostmillennial.com/erin-otoole-pledges-to-cancel-trudeaus-media-bailout/\u00a0\u2026 |url=https://twitter.com/erinotoolemp/status/1223614891896033281 |website=Twitter |language=en |date=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n:;Foreign\n:*Support creating a [[CANZUK]] agreement on trade<ref>{{cite web |title=CANZUK Deal |url=https://erinotoole.ca/canzuk/ |website=Erin O'Toole |access-date=7 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504033025/http://erinotoole.ca/canzuk/ |archive-date=4 May 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref><br>\n:;Social\n:*Criminalize blocking railways, airports, ports, or major roads, or entrances to businesses or households<ref>{{cite news |title=Erin O\u2019Toole: This is how I would get our country working again {{!}} National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/opinion/erin-otoole-this-is-how-i-would-make-this-country-work |date=26 February 2020 |language=en-CA}}</ref><br>\n:*Use [[Section 33 of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms|the notwithstanding clause]] to impose mandatory minimum sentences for violent crime<ref>{{cite news |title=Jason Kenney endorses Erin O\u2019Toole for leadership of Conservative party {{!}} National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/canada-news-pmn/otoole-mackay-set-to-kick-conservative-leadership-campaigns-up-a-notch |date=5 March 2020 |language=en-CA}}</ref>\n{{Endorsements box\n|df=yes| title = Endorsements of Erin O'Toole\n| list =\n;'''MPs:'''\n*[[Garnett Genuis]] (MP for [[Sherwood Park\u2014Fort Saskatchewan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/notes/garnett-genuis/my-choice-for-conservative-leader/2759957230720081/|title=My Choice for Conservative Leader &#124; Facebook|website=facebook.com}}</ref>\n*[[Dane Lloyd]] (MP for [[Sturgeon River\u2014Parkland]])<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/DaneLloydCPC/videos/183605969589828// Dane Lloyd], Facebook</ref>\n*[[Greg McLean (politician)|Greg McLean]]