able'' due to the latter's postponement, so not listed in the ''Radio Times'', but listed as a ''Wednesday Play'' in the BFI database.\n| missing\n|-\n| 27 January 1965\n| [[Fable (TV play)|Fable]]\n| John Hopkins\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nChristopher Morahan (D)\n| Ronald Lacey<br />Eileen Atkins<br />Thomas Baptiste<br />Barbara Assoon<br />Keith Barron\n| Postponed from 20 January 1965.\n| Yes (35mm tr?)\n|-\n| 3 February 1965\n| Dan, Dan, the Charity Man\n| Hugh Whitemore\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nDon Taylor (D)\n| Barry Foster<br />Ernest Clark<br />Philip Locke<br />Dora Reisser\n| Repeated under ''Encore'' on BBC2 01/10/1965.\n| missing\n|-\n| 10 February 1965\n| Ashes to Ashes\n| Marc Brandel\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nAlan Cooke (D)\n| Toby Robins<br />Scott Forbes\n| \n| Yes (16mm tr)\n|-\n| 17 February 1965\n| Wear a Very Big Hat\n| Eric Coltart\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nKenneth Loach (D)\n| Neville Smith<br />Sheila Fearn<br />William Holmes<br />Johnny Clive\n| Repeated under ''Encore'' on BBC2 24/09/1965.\n| missing\n|-\n| 24 February 1965\n| The Confidence Course\n| Dennis Potter\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nGilchrist Calder (D)\n| Dennis Price<br />Stanley Baxter\n| \n| missing\n|-\n| 3 March 1965\n| Campaign for One\n| Marielaine Douglas and Anthony Church\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nMoira Armstrong (D)\n| Barry Foster<br />Jeremy Kemp<br />David Bauer<br />Jerry Stovin\n| Repeated under ''Encore'' on BBC2 03/09/1965.\n| missing\n|-\n| 10 March 1965\n| Horror of Darkness\n| John Hopkins\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nAnthony Page (D)\n| Alfred Lynch<br />Nicol Williamson<br />Glenda Jackson\n| \n| Yes (35mm tr?)\n|-\n| 17 March 1965\n| A Little Temptation\n| Thomas Clarke\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nPeter Duguid (D)\n| Barbara Jefford<br />Denholm Elliott<br />Caroline Mortimer\n| Recorded in the BBC's Glasgow studios\n| Yes (35mm tr?)\n|-\n| 24 March 1965\n| Moving On\n| Bill Mellen\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nBrian Parker (D)\n| Peter Jeffrey<br />David Collings<br />God