se Feet?\n| David Mercer\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nDon Taylor (D)\n| David Markham<br />Willoughby Goddard<br />Patrick Troughton<br />Sylvia Kay<br />Jo Rowbottom<br />Victor Lucas\n| \n| Yes (35mm tr)\n|-\n| 9 June 1965\n| The Man Without Papers\n| Troy Kennedy Martin\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nPeter Duguid (D)\n| Benito Carruthers<br />Geraldine McEwan<br />James Maxwell<br />Charles Victor<br />Ingrid Hafner<br />John Woodnutt\n| \n| partial\n|-\n| 16 June 1965\n| The Pistol\n| A novel by James Jones.\nAdapted for television by Troy Kennedy Martin and Roger Smith. \n| James MacTaggart (P)\nJames Ferman (D)\n| Clive Endersby<br />John Brandon<br />Hal Galili\n| Repeated under ''Encore'' on BBC2 10/09/1965.\n| Yes (35mm tr?)\n|-\n| 30 June 1965\n| The Seven O'Clock Crunch\n| David Stone\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nToby Robertson (D)\n| Nigel Stock<br />Peter Jeffrey<br />Zena Walker<br />Jan Waters\n| \n| missing\n|-\n| 13 October 1965\n| Alice\n| Dennis Potter\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nGareth Davies (D)\n| George Baker<br />Rosalie Crutchley<br />David Langton<br />Deborah Watling\n| \n| Yes (35mm tr)\n|-\n| 20 October 1965\n| The Girl Who Loved Robots\n| Peter Everett\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nBrian Parker (D)\n| Dudley Foster<br />Isobel Black<br />Norman Rodway\n| \n| missing\n|-\n| 27 October 1965\n| A Designing Woman\n| Julia Jones\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nBrian Parker (D)\n| Reginald Marsh<br />Rhoda Lewis<br />John Collin\n| \n| missing\n|-\n| 3 November 1965\n| [[Up the Junction (The Wednesday Play)|Up the Junction]]\n| Nell Dunn\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nKenneth Loach (D)\n| Carol White<br />Geraldine Sherman<br />Vickery Turner<br />Tony Selby<br />Michael Standing<br />Ray Barron<br />Rita Webb<br />Hilda Barry<br />Jessie Robins\n| Repeated also 14/07/1993 on BBC2.\n| Yes (35mm tr?)\n|-\n| 10 November 1965\n| The Trial and Torture of Sir John Rampayne\n| Alan Seymour\n| James MacTaggart (P)\nPeter Duguid (D)\n| Jack Hawkins<br />Ian McKellen<br />Faith Brook<b